CHECK IF INSTALLED WITH
  $ gpio -v

To INSTALL WIRING PI use:
  $ wget https://project-downloads.drogon.net/wiringpi-latest.deb
  $ sudo dpkg -i wiringpi-latest.deb
  $ rm wiringpi-latest.deb

NOTES:
  I used on Raspbian GNU/Linux 11 (bullseye)
  

To ENABLE I2C use:
  $ sudo raspi-config
    > 3 Interface Options
    > I5 I2C
    > Yes
    > OK
    > Finish (ESC)

Notes:
  After this, if it doesnt immediatly work, give her a sudo reboot.
